# Research Radar

Research Radar is a small Python pipeline that fetches papers from bioRxiv, arXiv, and PubMed, normalizes them into one schema, deduplicates them, classifies them into topic buckets, and exports static JSON files for a Hugo site.

## What v1 does

- Fetches recent papers or backfill date ranges from `bioRxiv`, `arXiv`, and `PubMed`
- Normalizes records into one canonical schema
- Deduplicates by DOI, source identifiers, and normalized title plus first-author/year checks
- Classifies papers with rule-based keyword buckets
- Computes recent papers, topic counts over time, keyword frequency over time, and rising keywords
- Stores canonical history in SQLite and exports static JSON into Hugo `data/`

## Repository layout

```text
research-radar/
